Definition.WordDefinition: Missy \Mis"sy\, n. An affectionate, or contemptuous, form of miss; a young girl; a miss. -- a. Like a miss, or girl. [1913 Webster]
missy n : a young woman; "a young lady of 18" [syn: {girl}, {miss}, {young lady}, {young woman}, {fille}]
